sfField.summary: If Auto Close is enabled, the number of days until a service request with this type is auto closed.
Check box to enable auto close. If enabled, the system will auto close any service requests of this type automatically.
This checkbox will determine if scheduling hours should be considered when applying for a new schedule on a type.
Check this box if the current service type is meant to be flagged as a scheduled collection type.
Indicates the # of available schedules that will be displayed as buttons in the 311 Console App during service request creation (acceptable #'s: 0, 1, 3, 5).
If checked, the SLA will be restarted when a service request is transferred to this service request type.
The # of service requests of this type that may be scheduled for a specific location per month.
The # of service requests of this type that may be scheduled for a specific location per year.

The minimum # of days in advance that a schedule must be submitted. For example, if the value is 3, a citizen must submit a service request a minimum of 3 days in advance of the next available schedule date.
If enabled, duplicate requests for a location will be blocked.
This should be a JSON snippet for matching a geo layer field to a Schedule Zone value for scheduling. Example:\n{"zone": {"layer_name":"Layer-Name-Goes-Here", "layer_value":"Layer-Value-Goes-Here"}}
The range of days in which schedules may be available (e.g. a value of 90 would mean the system will look for all available schedules for a location within the next 90 days).
Description of types available for scheduled pickup: \nItems - the number of items to pick up\nRequests - the number of requests
The description of this service request type that will appear in the 311 Console App during service request creation.
If enabled, service requests of this type will require a location be provided for the service request to be created.
Check this box to capture the scheduled date as the expected finish date for service requests of this type.
Enables a calendar picker widget on the service request creation screen in the 311 Console app.

Service request that would be generated only by system functions (automated processes). If checked, the service request type will not appear in any service request creation menus (Agent Console, Web, Mobile).
Allows this service request to be transferred to any other service request.
If checked, all the attachments on service requests are not visible on web or mobile and are hidden from integrators using the API. This flag takes precedence over similar flag on STV
